    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing our highest offensive floor. At an 81.48 score, he remains a must-start against the generous xERA of Pallante; his elite xwOBA of 0.393 and favorable batting order placement insulate him against even the most adverse park factors. Joining him in the elite tier is **Hyeseong Kim** (70.53), whose value is significantly amplified by the combination of a high-ceiling matchup against Feltner and a 100% stolen base efficiency rating against the opponent's delivery. Similarly, **Colt Keith** (69.64) benefits from a 13% SP skill bump, positioning him as our premier infield play today.\n\nWhile the volatility of facing elite arms like Sale and Skenes necessitates some caution, the optimizer remains aggressive on speed-focused profiles. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (65.41) earns his spot specifically due to the 92% SB success rate against a slow-delivery opponent, and **Carson Benge** (63.10) provides high utility from the leadoff spot. The most difficult personnel decision involved **Josh Smith**, who scored a 41.70. While he offered a strong dynamic platoon edge against Kirby, his suboptimal batting position and the overall strength of our starting middle infielders\u2014**Chase Meidroth** (57.73) and **Trea Turner** (55.23)\u2014relegated him to the bench. We are also closely monitoring the pending lineups for **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Hyeseong Kim**; should they slide lower in their respective batting orders, their scores will require re-evaluation before first pitch.\n\nRisks today are concentrated in our encounters with upper-echelon pitching. **Caleb Durbin** (43.74) faces Skubal, a significant test, but his utility as a stolen base threat keeps him marginally viable. Furthermore, **Kyle Schwarber** (53.83) and **Junior Caminero** (55.03) must contend with the respective difficulties of Sale and Skenes. While the raw projections for these players are tempered by these SP matchups, the 5x5 Roto need for counting stats necessitates their presence in the lineup despite the sub-60 efficiency scores. We remain at full health for active rostered players, with **Christian Yelich** and **Victor Scott II** continuing to occupy bench slots due to availability issues, and **Zac Veen** remaining in the minors.",
